<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6196&amp;p=58709#p58709"><![CDATA[
NOR flash media like GBC and GBA flash cards is typically sold by the bit. Divide it by 8 to get the capacity in bytes. This means the products you mention are 8 MiB or 4 MiB in size. But yes, they should accept Game Boy ROMs with no problem; that's what they're designed for.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Mar 21, 2010 4:42 am</p><hr />
