<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6196&amp;p=58674#p58674</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6196&amp;p=58674#p58674"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[how to...]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6196&amp;p=58674#p58674"><![CDATA[
A Game Boy Color flash card should work in a Game Boy, Super Game Boy, Game Boy Pocket, Game Boy Color, Game Boy Advance, Game Boy Advance SP, or Game Boy Player. But by the time I got into GBA development (November 2001), GBC flash cards were already hard to find.<br /><br />A GBA flash card such as the FireLinker or SuperCard should work in a GBA, GBA SP, GB Player, GB micro, DS, or DS Lite. To use GB or GBC software on a GBA flash card, you use the "Goomba Color" emulator. It's not an entirely accurate emulation due to the GBA's limitations, but it is still Running On Real Nintendo Hardware.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Mar 20, 2010 5:04 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
